The 2018 edition of the Lagos International Food and Beverage Fair and Festival (LIFBEF), scheduled for July 26 to 29, has been postponed till September 27-30. A statement by the Convener and Managing Partner of Imani Events and Exhibitions, Khadijah Tebun, said the postponement is “due to our desire to give the 2018 edition world class standard. And to satisfy the purpose of the initiative, the fair organizers deem it important to reschedule the event, to enable us accommodate various programs and plans, such that would make the event a memorable one.”